1
00:00:13,540 --> 00:00:15,780
♪Trap my frame♪

2
00:00:15,980 --> 00:00:20,060
♪Plagues demand I bow in shame♪

3
00:00:20,780 --> 00:00:22,940
♪Snare my soul♪

4
00:00:23,020 --> 00:00:27,100
♪Rules command I swallow my pride♪

5
00:00:27,260 --> 00:00:30,620
♪Mock my way♪

6
00:00:30,900 --> 00:00:34,060
♪Chained me where I must stay♪

7
00:00:34,420 --> 00:00:36,780
♪Taught me to kneel, not to speak♪

8
00:00:37,020 --> 00:00:41,220
♪And to let my life pass by in silence♪

9
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:44,100
♪But I heard the wind♪

10
00:00:44,220 --> 00:00:45,900
♪From the sea and the sky♪

11
00:00:46,180 --> 00:00:47,660
♪It said don't bend♪

12
00:00:47,780 --> 00:00:49,820
♪Bow your head, and your chains begin♪

13
00:00:49,940 --> 00:00:51,380
♪You are the wave♪

14
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:53,300
♪And the wind that won't behave♪

15
00:00:53,380 --> 00:00:56,340
♪How could you be chained?♪

16
00:00:56,740 --> 00:00:58,740
♪Untamed, uncaged, unclaimed♪

17
00:00:58,780 --> 00:01:00,540
♪You're the blade in my gaze♪

18
00:01:00,620 --> 00:01:02,420
♪This world will leave you no space♪

19
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:04,220
♪Then pierce it with your blaze♪

20
00:01:04,220 --> 00:01:06,100
♪My silent grind♪

21
00:01:06,100 --> 00:01:08,060
♪My aching pain♪

22
00:01:08,060 --> 00:01:10,300
♪Will one day turn...♪

23
00:01:11,860 --> 00:01:14,620
♪I am who I am♪

24
00:01:14,620 --> 00:01:18,140
♪My greatest ambition♪

25
00:01:18,220 --> 00:01:21,300
♪If the world can't contain me♪

26
00:01:21,380 --> 00:01:24,940
♪Then I'll break through it♪

27
00:01:25,420 --> 00:01:26,940
♪Become who I am♪

28
00:01:26,940 --> 00:01:28,260
[Wild Ambition Bloom]

29
00:01:28,260 --> 00:01:29,980
[Adapted from Stone and Water's novel,
The Uncaged Flame]

30
00:01:29,980 --> 00:01:32,980
[Episode 20]

31
00:01:34,940 --> 00:01:36,380
[Tian's Apothecary]

32
00:01:36,430 --> 00:01:38,380
But before the negotiations begin,

33
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:40,380
we must first acknowledge one thing.

34
00:01:40,590 --> 00:01:42,620
Although your lawyer said

35
00:01:42,870 --> 00:01:45,490
that two misprinted fliers
were distributed,

36
00:01:45,710 --> 00:01:46,410
in fact,

37
00:01:46,430 --> 00:01:48,660
there were

38
00:01:48,680 --> 00:01:49,770
four.

39
00:01:58,560 --> 00:01:59,540
I appreciate

40
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:01,290
your honesty.

41
00:02:02,280 --> 00:02:03,660
We messed up first.

42
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:04,820
If we lie now,

43
00:02:04,840 --> 00:02:06,380
it will just make things worse,
won't it?

44
00:02:08,190 --> 00:02:08,980
You've got

45
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:11,540
good judgment.

46
00:02:12,150 --> 00:02:12,890
Mr. Tian,

47
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:14,850
please take a look.

48
00:02:15,560 --> 00:02:18,220
Here's the statement
from the printing house manager.

49
00:02:18,430 --> 00:02:20,610
And here's the one from workers there.

50
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:24,690
Plus, here are the students' statements
who gave out the fliers.

51
00:02:25,750 --> 00:02:26,610
I'm not showing you these

52
00:02:26,630 --> 00:02:28,260
to shirk responsibility.

53
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:29,450
We just want to make it clear

54
00:02:29,630 --> 00:02:30,980
that the misprinting on these fliers

55
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:32,780
was an honest mistake by the workers.

56
00:02:33,080 --> 00:02:35,660
We had no intention
of infringing on your rights.

57
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:37,340
But regardless,

58
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:38,290
this incident

59
00:02:38,310 --> 00:02:40,610
still caused a loss to your interests.

60
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:42,850
So, we're here to offer

61
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:44,820
you

62
00:02:44,840 --> 00:02:46,290
and Professor Claudy

63
00:02:46,630 --> 00:02:48,220
our sincerest apologies.

64
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:53,410
That's all?

65
00:02:54,190 --> 00:02:55,340
We will also publish

66
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:56,980
a public apology in the newspaper.

67
00:02:58,030 --> 00:02:58,780
And of course,

68
00:02:59,080 --> 00:03:00,980
we'll compensate for all the losses

69
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:03,170
caused by this incident.

70
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:06,010
How much?

71
00:03:07,870 --> 00:03:08,780
Five thousand silver dollars.

72
00:03:15,590 --> 00:03:16,290
Tongdao,

73
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:17,570
I think...

74
00:03:18,190 --> 00:03:19,890
How many times have I told you?

75
00:03:19,910 --> 00:03:22,410
Call me Mr. Tian
when we're around others.

76
00:03:22,430 --> 00:03:23,060
Okay.

77
00:03:23,430 --> 00:03:24,780
Keep that in mind, okay?

78
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:26,170
Mr. Tian,

79
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:29,660
I think it's actually worth considering.

80
00:03:40,710 --> 00:03:43,500
Since you're being so upfront,

81
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:46,340
I'll be straight with you too.

82
00:03:47,590 --> 00:03:50,170
Even if you drop a bomb,

83
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:51,820
you at least

84
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:53,410
make some noise, right?

85
00:03:53,710 --> 00:03:56,130
But after your fliers went out,

86
00:03:56,150 --> 00:03:58,010
there was nothing, not a whisper.

87
00:03:58,190 --> 00:04:00,570
So they weren't even as effective
as a whisper, were they?

88
00:04:00,680 --> 00:04:02,570
Mr. Tian, you are absolutely right.

89
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:05,500
So since there was no harm,

90
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:07,780
there's no talk of losses, is there?

91
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:10,100
The reason I'm coming after you

92
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:11,100
and dragging you to court

93
00:04:11,430 --> 00:04:13,380
is to utterly destroy you.

94
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:16,220
And you know why?
What makes the Oriental Bunao Pill

95
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:18,610
so special that it's outselling ours?

96
00:04:18,630 --> 00:04:19,220
Right?

97
00:04:20,950 --> 00:04:22,930
Mr. Tian is frank

98
00:04:23,310 --> 00:04:24,290
and unconventional.

99
00:04:24,560 --> 00:04:25,730
That's for sure.

100
00:04:25,920 --> 00:04:28,250
In business,
being genuine is everything.

101
00:04:28,360 --> 00:04:29,660
But seeing

102
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:31,340
your humble attitude just now,

103
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:34,700
I have to say it's very satisfactory,

104
00:04:34,830 --> 00:04:35,610
so I've decided.

105
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:37,610
First off,

106
00:04:38,270 --> 00:04:39,660
you don't need to compensate us.

107
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:40,980
And second,

108
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:43,100
you don't need to apologize either.

109
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:45,370
Then...

110
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:48,810
I am willing to give you a chance

111
00:04:49,430 --> 00:04:50,410
to cooperate with me.

112
00:04:53,950 --> 00:04:54,780
Well...

113
00:04:58,240 --> 00:04:59,050
Well...

114
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:00,610
So, how do we do it?

115
00:05:01,190 --> 00:05:02,140
First,

116
00:05:03,430 --> 00:05:05,850
the Oriental Bunao Pill

117
00:05:05,870 --> 00:05:08,340
must be delisted from Jujing Apothecary.

118
00:05:08,360 --> 00:05:09,930
All raw materials

119
00:05:09,950 --> 00:05:12,490
must be sourced from Tian's Apothecary.

120
00:05:14,870 --> 00:05:15,540
That's...

121
00:05:17,070 --> 00:05:18,730
We've got a cooperation agreement

122
00:05:18,750 --> 00:05:20,700
with Mr. Xia Yuan.

123
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:23,410
Then breach it.

124
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:25,490
The amount for breaking the contract...

125
00:05:25,750 --> 00:05:27,340
I'll make up
for whatever you're short of.

126
00:05:29,630 --> 00:05:30,980
It's not about money.

127
00:05:32,430 --> 00:05:33,580
It's business.

128
00:05:34,510 --> 00:05:36,340
What can't be settled with money?

129
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:37,900
Right.

130
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:38,980
And one more thing.

131
00:05:39,510 --> 00:05:42,410
You must file a complaint
with the TCM Guild,

132
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:45,900
saying that Shouyuan Apothecary
sells inferior goods as superior

133
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:46,980
and mixes real and fake ones.

134
00:05:48,510 --> 00:05:49,220
Mr. Tian,

135
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:51,730
you're asking us
to make something up, aren't you?

136
00:05:51,750 --> 00:05:53,340
This is a much better option.

137
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:54,580
It's way better

138
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:57,290
than me relentlessly pursuing you
in court

139
00:05:57,310 --> 00:05:59,020
until you're ruined

140
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:01,660
and bankrupt,

141
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:02,250
right?

142
00:06:02,270 --> 00:06:04,410
But we don't have much of a reputation
or many assets to begin with.

143
00:06:04,860 --> 00:06:06,020
You don't get a say here.

144
00:06:10,940 --> 00:06:11,860
What do you say?

145
00:06:12,140 --> 00:06:14,060
Will you work with me,

146
00:06:14,340 --> 00:06:16,900
or go against me?

147
00:06:24,180 --> 00:06:25,060
Dear,

148
00:06:25,780 --> 00:06:26,620
it's up to you.

149
00:06:27,580 --> 00:06:28,300
Say something.

150
00:06:35,500 --> 00:06:36,300
Mr. Tian,

151
00:06:37,380 --> 00:06:38,700
although Wen's Pharmacy

152
00:06:39,100 --> 00:06:40,300
is a small pharmacy,

153
00:06:41,500 --> 00:06:44,780
we're an honest business after all.

154
00:06:45,220 --> 00:06:46,220
So I gave it some thought.

155
00:06:47,140 --> 00:06:48,060
Standing against you

156
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:49,660
feels truer to who we are.

157
00:06:50,140 --> 00:06:51,620
You truly don't know

158
00:06:51,620 --> 00:06:52,820
when you've got it good, huh?

159
00:06:52,820 --> 00:06:53,620
Tian Tongdao,

160
00:06:53,780 --> 00:06:55,540
you're not even fit to carry our bags.

161
00:06:55,860 --> 00:06:56,740
In terms of efficacy,

162
00:06:56,820 --> 00:06:58,140
the Oriental Bunao Pill

163
00:06:58,300 --> 00:06:59,860
far surpasses the Western Bunao Pill.

164
00:06:59,980 --> 00:07:01,700
And we're much lower on price.

165
00:07:01,820 --> 00:07:02,860
As for sales strategy,

166
00:07:02,980 --> 00:07:04,380
we're more agile than you.

167
00:07:04,380 --> 00:07:05,940
As for market trends,

168
00:07:05,940 --> 00:07:07,340
we will soon be ahead of you.

169
00:07:07,660 --> 00:07:08,580
Do you understand?

170
00:07:11,820 --> 00:07:12,700
What the heck?

171
00:07:12,700 --> 00:07:13,940
Let's go, dear.

172
00:07:16,940 --> 00:07:17,740
You...

173
00:07:18,140 --> 00:07:19,500
Gentlemen,

174
00:07:20,100 --> 00:07:22,340
then we'll see each other in court.

175
00:07:23,940 --> 00:07:24,580
Hey, you...

176
00:07:26,820 --> 00:07:27,460
Tongxin.

177
00:07:28,100 --> 00:07:28,700
Tongdao.

178
00:07:30,660 --> 00:07:32,620
Were they just trying to piss me off?

179
00:07:33,460 --> 00:07:34,140
Well...

180
00:07:36,060 --> 00:07:36,940
Calm down, Tongdao.

181
00:07:37,900 --> 00:07:40,820
[Wen's Pharmacy]

182
00:07:40,980 --> 00:07:41,580
Mr. Wen.

183
00:07:41,620 --> 00:07:43,340
The shopkeeper of Jujing Apothecary
is waiting for you inside.

184
00:07:46,740 --> 00:07:47,540
Sir,

185
00:07:48,180 --> 00:07:48,820
why are you here?

186
00:07:49,660 --> 00:07:50,820
Mr. Xia sent me over

187
00:07:50,820 --> 00:07:52,020
with two things for you.

188
00:07:52,820 --> 00:07:54,100
He knows you've poured everything

189
00:07:54,100 --> 00:07:55,300
you've got into the business.

190
00:07:55,380 --> 00:07:57,340
But lawsuits will bleed you dry.

191
00:07:57,940 --> 00:07:59,900
He gave me some money to pass on to you.

192
00:08:02,020 --> 00:08:03,700
He said if it doesn't cover everything,

193
00:08:03,860 --> 00:08:04,740
just let him know.

194
00:08:04,900 --> 00:08:05,940
Just win the case.

195
00:08:06,300 --> 00:08:07,220
Money's the least of your concerns.

196
00:08:08,660 --> 00:08:09,300
Well...

197
00:08:14,460 --> 00:08:15,420
Please tell Mr. Xia we're grateful.

198
00:08:16,780 --> 00:08:17,660
We appreciate it.

199
00:08:18,300 --> 00:08:20,420
[Lin Chunbai]
Here's attorney Li Chunbai's card.

200
00:08:21,220 --> 00:08:22,300
Mr. Xia arranged for him

201
00:08:23,220 --> 00:08:24,300
to handle the case

202
00:08:24,420 --> 00:08:25,420
and support you throughout the lawsuit.

203
00:08:26,420 --> 00:08:27,420
Mr. Lin? The attorney?

204
00:08:27,740 --> 00:08:28,340
Indeed.

205
00:08:29,380 --> 00:08:30,420
Mr. Lin will be waiting for you

206
00:08:31,020 --> 00:08:32,660
at his law firm

207
00:08:32,660 --> 00:08:33,340
tomorrow at 10 AM.

208
00:08:33,540 --> 00:08:34,500
Please be on time.

209
00:08:34,740 --> 00:08:35,540
We will.

210
00:08:36,500 --> 00:08:37,220
Thank you.

211
00:08:37,460 --> 00:08:38,260
I'll take my leave.

212
00:08:38,820 --> 00:08:39,460
Take care.

213
00:08:41,140 --> 00:08:41,820
See him out.

214
00:08:42,140 --> 00:08:42,620
Okay.

215
00:08:43,940 --> 00:08:44,540
Please take care.

216
00:08:45,820 --> 00:08:46,380
How is it?

217
00:08:46,860 --> 00:08:48,380
Do you still feel confident
about this case?

218
00:08:50,100 --> 00:08:51,060
Sure, we might not win.

219
00:08:51,300 --> 00:08:51,980
But

220
00:08:52,820 --> 00:08:54,300
that doesn't mean we'll lose.

221
00:08:57,260 --> 00:08:57,980
What do you mean?

222
00:08:58,260 --> 00:09:00,740
We're not fighting to win the lawsuit,

223
00:09:00,740 --> 00:09:01,620
but the market.

224
00:09:04,340 --> 00:09:05,620
The truth is,
if we really wanted to win the case,

225
00:09:05,620 --> 00:09:06,700
we could.

226
00:09:06,700 --> 00:09:07,300
Really?

227
00:09:08,260 --> 00:09:09,700
We've been overlooking someone here.

228
00:09:10,260 --> 00:09:10,980
Who?

229
00:09:11,540 --> 00:09:12,540
Professor Claudy.

230
00:09:18,980 --> 00:09:19,740
[Tianxing Inn]

231
00:09:19,740 --> 00:09:21,260
[Pilot Cafe]

232
00:09:21,660 --> 00:09:22,820
Professor, please.

233
00:09:25,100 --> 00:09:26,060
You've had enough to drink.

234
00:09:26,060 --> 00:09:27,300
You can't have any more.

235
00:09:27,300 --> 00:09:28,140
- Professor.
- I'm fine.

236
00:09:28,780 --> 00:09:30,100
We've got
something important tomorrow morning.

237
00:09:30,580 --> 00:09:31,940
We're meeting with the lawyer, remember?

238
00:09:32,460 --> 00:09:35,260
I'm not meeting anyone
until I've had my fill.

239
00:09:35,860 --> 00:09:36,740
When will you have had enough?

240
00:09:37,620 --> 00:09:39,100
Just promise me one last drink, okay?

241
00:09:39,220 --> 00:09:39,860
One last drink.

242
00:09:40,220 --> 00:09:41,260
Just bring it over.

243
00:09:41,260 --> 00:09:41,860
Quick.

244
00:09:43,100 --> 00:09:44,220
Sir, excuse me.

245
00:09:44,220 --> 00:09:46,060
Are you Mr. Huang
from Tian's Apothecary?

246
00:09:46,060 --> 00:09:46,460
That's right.

247
00:09:46,460 --> 00:09:47,340
You have a phone call.

248
00:09:47,900 --> 00:09:48,300
Me?

249
00:09:48,300 --> 00:09:49,260
Yes, over there.

250
00:09:49,540 --> 00:09:50,100
Please.

251
00:09:56,260 --> 00:09:56,900
Who is this?

252
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:02,980
You can't even recognize my voice?

253
00:10:03,580 --> 00:10:04,340
Taohong?

254
00:10:07,060 --> 00:10:08,940
Is she the only one you think about?

255
00:10:11,900 --> 00:10:12,700
Linglong.

256
00:10:17,380 --> 00:10:19,620
Got any baijiu? I could use a glass.

257
00:10:20,220 --> 00:10:21,020
Apologies, Sir.

258
00:10:21,140 --> 00:10:22,340
We don't have that here.

259
00:10:23,740 --> 00:10:24,660
Impossible.

260
00:10:25,980 --> 00:10:30,380
Every tavern
in Northeast China has baijiu.

261
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:32,140
Sir, this is Shanghai.

262
00:10:32,740 --> 00:10:33,860
Oops.

263
00:10:34,860 --> 00:10:37,700
Right, Shanghai, not Northeast China.

264
00:10:43,300 --> 00:10:44,540
You really like baijiu, huh?

265
00:10:44,780 --> 00:10:45,660
No, not really.

266
00:10:46,220 --> 00:10:47,900
But it's the only thing

267
00:10:48,340 --> 00:10:51,700
that helps me forget the pain
of being away from Natasha.

268
00:10:55,860 --> 00:10:56,980
Who is Natasha?

269
00:10:58,140 --> 00:10:58,980
Give him another one.

270
00:10:59,100 --> 00:11:00,460
Who are you?

271
00:11:01,940 --> 00:11:02,820
Professor Claudy,

272
00:11:04,060 --> 00:11:06,580
I am Wen Zhiqiu from Wen's Pharmacy.

273
00:11:07,060 --> 00:11:07,860
Hello.

274
00:11:11,020 --> 00:11:11,660
Hello?

275
00:11:13,620 --> 00:11:14,580
If you're not going
to tell me your name,

276
00:11:14,580 --> 00:11:15,500
I'm hanging up.

277
00:11:16,140 --> 00:11:16,620
No, wait.

278
00:11:17,220 --> 00:11:18,900
Try thinking a little harder.

279
00:11:21,460 --> 00:11:22,420
Liu Wan'er?

280
00:11:23,020 --> 00:11:23,740
Perhaps.

281
00:11:23,740 --> 00:11:25,300
How dare you even call me?

282
00:11:26,580 --> 00:11:27,340
I'm telling you,

283
00:11:27,900 --> 00:11:29,500
I won't fall for your tricks again.

284
00:11:29,780 --> 00:11:30,740
That's what happened.

285
00:11:31,620 --> 00:11:32,940
So, I really hope

286
00:11:32,940 --> 00:11:36,500
you can forgive us.

287
00:11:40,780 --> 00:11:42,580
I forgive you.

288
00:11:45,260 --> 00:11:45,940
Thank you.

289
00:11:46,740 --> 00:11:49,300
Tolerance is not something

290
00:11:50,780 --> 00:11:52,780
that those who lack it deserve.

291
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:56,100
Sir.

292
00:11:58,060 --> 00:11:58,660
Here.

293
00:12:03,340 --> 00:12:04,740
You understand?

294
00:12:06,020 --> 00:12:07,540
Understand what?

295
00:12:13,260 --> 00:12:15,060
♪Go to sleep♪

296
00:12:15,780 --> 00:12:21,580
♪Baby mice and baby bears♪

297
00:12:22,380 --> 00:12:27,300
♪Everyone's sleeping through the night♪

298
00:12:27,580 --> 00:12:28,300
What are you playing at?

299
00:12:29,260 --> 00:12:30,180
I'm warning you.

300
00:12:30,300 --> 00:12:31,460
Don't come for me ever again.

301
00:12:31,460 --> 00:12:33,300
Let's just stay
out of each other's business.

302
00:12:33,300 --> 00:12:34,380
If you really push me too far,

303
00:12:34,380 --> 00:12:35,460
I'll go straight to your husband.

304
00:12:35,460 --> 00:12:36,460
Worst case, we'll

305
00:12:36,460 --> 00:12:37,100
go down together.

306
00:12:49,700 --> 00:12:52,860
♪Flying high up in the sky♪

307
00:12:55,420 --> 00:12:57,780
♪In the moonbeams' silvery glow♪

308
00:12:57,780 --> 00:12:58,460
Let's go.

309
00:12:58,460 --> 00:12:59,100
Hurry up.

310
00:12:59,340 --> 00:13:00,060
Stop singing.

311
00:13:00,060 --> 00:13:01,340
I'm not going.

312
00:13:01,500 --> 00:13:02,180
You've had too much to drink.

313
00:13:02,180 --> 00:13:04,780
I'm not finished singing
"Green Carriage"

314
00:13:04,780 --> 00:13:06,140
for Natasha yet.

315
00:13:06,140 --> 00:13:06,540
Let's go.

316
00:13:06,540 --> 00:13:07,220
Goodbye.

317
00:13:07,220 --> 00:13:08,140
- Bye-bye.
- Goodbye.

318
00:13:20,460 --> 00:13:21,180
How was it?

319
00:13:22,860 --> 00:13:24,220
Was it too rushed for you?

320
00:13:24,580 --> 00:13:25,500
But I did my best.

321
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:26,740
I chatted with him for a few minutes.

322
00:13:26,900 --> 00:13:27,660
Whatever I said

323
00:13:27,660 --> 00:13:29,020
must've hit a nerve.

324
00:13:29,260 --> 00:13:31,140
He just hung up on me.

325
00:13:31,620 --> 00:13:33,820
How did your conversation
with Professor Claudy go?

326
00:13:35,060 --> 00:13:36,180
Didn't get to talk about anything.

327
00:13:36,380 --> 00:13:37,140
He's drunk.

328
00:13:38,540 --> 00:13:40,380
So, should we think of another way?

329
00:13:44,220 --> 00:13:45,980
There's one thing I can't figure out.

330
00:13:46,180 --> 00:13:46,900
What is it?

331
00:13:48,620 --> 00:13:50,140
Professor Claudy

332
00:13:50,300 --> 00:13:51,980
is a famous American scholar.

333
00:13:52,940 --> 00:13:55,580
Why does he speak Russian

334
00:13:55,580 --> 00:13:56,500
and sing Russian songs when he's drunk?

335
00:14:02,100 --> 00:14:04,460
[Western Bunao Pill. Tian's Apothecary]

336
00:14:13,380 --> 00:14:14,220
Come on, this way.

337
00:14:16,820 --> 00:14:17,820
It's your first time here.

338
00:14:18,580 --> 00:14:19,820
Let me introduce you to some friends.

339
00:14:19,820 --> 00:14:20,380
Okay.

340
00:14:22,300 --> 00:14:22,860
Come.

341
00:14:23,660 --> 00:14:24,980
Having a good chat, ladies?

342
00:14:26,180 --> 00:14:27,100
Mrs. Tian.

343
00:14:27,500 --> 00:14:28,420
This is Mrs. Gu.

344
00:14:28,420 --> 00:14:29,340
Hello, Mrs. Gu.

345
00:14:29,460 --> 00:14:30,580
This is Mrs. Zhou.

346
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:31,420
Hello.

347
00:14:31,620 --> 00:14:32,420
Miss Yan.

348
00:14:32,820 --> 00:14:34,020
Nice to meet you, Miss Yan.

349
00:14:34,260 --> 00:14:35,300
This is Miss Bai.

350
00:14:35,460 --> 00:14:36,460
She's Tongxin's friend.

351
00:14:37,380 --> 00:14:38,620
She's that movie star, isn't she?

352
00:14:38,620 --> 00:14:39,340
Yes, it's her.

353
00:14:40,380 --> 00:14:42,660
She's much prettier in real life.

354
00:14:43,060 --> 00:14:44,260
Even more beautiful than on the posters.

355
00:14:44,260 --> 00:14:45,060
Thank you.

356
00:14:45,380 --> 00:14:46,980
So, how are movies made?

357
00:14:47,220 --> 00:14:48,780
If you'd like,

358
00:14:48,980 --> 00:14:49,900
I can take you all

359
00:14:49,900 --> 00:14:51,460
to the set sometime.

360
00:14:51,740 --> 00:14:53,060
- Great!
- Great!

361
00:14:54,420 --> 00:14:55,460
By the way, Caiyun,

362
00:14:55,460 --> 00:14:56,820
when are you going to America?

363
00:14:57,100 --> 00:14:57,900
In September.

364
00:14:58,780 --> 00:15:00,100
Is it Columbia University?

365
00:15:00,700 --> 00:15:01,300
Yes, it is.

366
00:15:01,460 --> 00:15:02,380
What are you studying?

367
00:15:02,540 --> 00:15:03,220
Chemistry.

368
00:15:03,460 --> 00:15:04,420
That is good.

369
00:15:04,420 --> 00:15:05,820
Chemistry is very popular now.

370
00:15:06,220 --> 00:15:07,060
I need to use the bathroom.

371
00:15:07,060 --> 00:15:08,260
Why would a girl study that?

372
00:15:08,260 --> 00:15:09,300
Go in on the first floor,
then turn left.

373
00:15:09,300 --> 00:15:09,980
Okay, thanks.

374
00:15:11,180 --> 00:15:12,420
It's quite popular abroad.

375
00:15:12,420 --> 00:15:13,540
When are you coming back?

376
00:15:16,540 --> 00:15:18,180
You idiot!

377
00:15:18,900 --> 00:15:19,460
I was wrong.

378
00:15:19,740 --> 00:15:21,340
I told you to keep an eye on Wen Zhiqiu,

379
00:15:21,340 --> 00:15:22,700
and make sure he couldn't talk to him.

380
00:15:22,820 --> 00:15:23,780
What were you doing?

381
00:15:23,780 --> 00:15:25,260
How did they manage to chat?

382
00:15:25,900 --> 00:15:27,020
I promise

383
00:15:27,020 --> 00:15:28,260
I only walked away for like one minute.

384
00:15:28,260 --> 00:15:30,340
They started talking in just one minute?

385
00:15:30,340 --> 00:15:31,540
Bend over the table, hands down,
and stick your butt out.

386
00:15:31,940 --> 00:15:32,620
Mr. Tian, I was wrong.

387
00:15:32,620 --> 00:15:33,060
Stick it out higher!

388
00:15:33,060 --> 00:15:33,860
It was my fault!

389
00:15:34,540 --> 00:15:36,580
One minute, you say?

390
00:15:36,740 --> 00:15:37,740
One minute, huh?

391
00:15:37,740 --> 00:15:39,180
Stop! It's like this.

392
00:15:39,180 --> 00:15:39,780
I... He...

393
00:15:39,780 --> 00:15:40,660
I guarantee you,

394
00:15:40,740 --> 00:15:41,900
he didn't get to talk

395
00:15:41,900 --> 00:15:42,700
to Wen Zhiqiu.

396
00:15:42,700 --> 00:15:43,660
How do you know?

397
00:15:43,660 --> 00:15:44,740
Didn't you leave?

398
00:15:45,700 --> 00:15:47,100
He was drunk

399
00:15:47,260 --> 00:15:48,500
and singing.

400
00:15:48,580 --> 00:15:49,460
What song was he singing?

401
00:15:49,940 --> 00:15:51,420
Wait, let me think.

402
00:15:52,020 --> 00:15:54,020
It wasn't

403
00:15:54,140 --> 00:15:55,020
an English song.

404
00:15:55,780 --> 00:15:57,020
You useless fool!

405
00:15:57,020 --> 00:15:58,580
Really, it wasn't an English song,
I promise.

406
00:15:58,580 --> 00:16:00,420
You think you got off easy, huh?

407
00:16:00,420 --> 00:16:02,300
It wasn't an English song, huh?

408
00:16:02,300 --> 00:16:02,780
Mr. Tian!

409
00:16:02,780 --> 00:16:03,300
You ruined my big plan!

410
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:04,700
I was wrong, Mr. Tian! Please stop!

411
00:16:04,700 --> 00:16:05,620
You fool!

412
00:16:05,620 --> 00:16:06,380
Please give me one more chance!

413
00:16:06,380 --> 00:16:07,740
Grab your stuff and get out of here!

414
00:16:07,740 --> 00:16:09,300
Mr. Tian, I promise,

415
00:16:09,300 --> 00:16:10,980
I will solve this problem.

416
00:16:11,140 --> 00:16:12,180
- I'll solve it.
- Come,

417
00:16:12,180 --> 00:16:13,340
stand here.

418
00:16:13,820 --> 00:16:14,420
Come back.

419
00:16:14,460 --> 00:16:15,660
I won't hit you. Come here!

420
00:16:15,660 --> 00:16:16,540
Really, Mr. Tian?

421
00:16:16,540 --> 00:16:16,980
I...

422
00:16:16,980 --> 00:16:18,500
You heard what I said.

423
00:16:18,500 --> 00:16:19,100
Stand here.

424
00:16:19,100 --> 00:16:20,340
I was wrong. Please give me a chance.

425
00:16:20,340 --> 00:16:21,140
I can fix this.

426
00:16:21,140 --> 00:16:21,980
Just one more chance.

427
00:16:23,420 --> 00:16:24,060
Get out!

428
00:16:24,980 --> 00:16:25,980
You idiot!

429
00:16:26,300 --> 00:16:28,100
You couldn't even handle that?

430
00:16:28,420 --> 00:16:29,980
I wish you'd just disappear!

431
00:16:34,220 --> 00:16:36,660
You're back.
Haven't grabbed a bite yet, huh?

432
00:16:37,300 --> 00:16:39,220
I made fish today.

433
00:16:40,260 --> 00:16:41,300
Saved half just for you.

434
00:16:42,140 --> 00:16:43,020
It's extra fresh, I promise.

435
00:16:43,740 --> 00:16:44,980
You saved me some again?

436
00:16:46,940 --> 00:16:48,420
What's wrong? Did you eat yet?

437
00:16:50,780 --> 00:16:51,940
I was just over at the Tians'.

438
00:16:53,820 --> 00:16:54,700
Did they treat you badly?

439
00:16:56,100 --> 00:16:56,740
No.

440
00:16:57,540 --> 00:16:58,780
If they look down on you,

441
00:16:59,100 --> 00:17:00,100
I'll go and tell them off.

442
00:17:01,060 --> 00:17:01,980
Don't worry.

443
00:17:05,260 --> 00:17:06,900
I won't let it get to me.

444
00:17:10,340 --> 00:17:11,220
What are you busy with?

445
00:17:12,060 --> 00:17:14,100
[Unpaid Dues]
I'm organizing Mr. Lin's materials

446
00:17:14,420 --> 00:17:15,540
for tomorrow.

447
00:17:17,580 --> 00:17:19,220
You settled the bills for the silk shop

448
00:17:20,780 --> 00:17:22,740
and the tailor's for me?

449
00:17:23,860 --> 00:17:25,460
I also paid the rent

450
00:17:25,580 --> 00:17:26,540
for the next quarter.

451
00:17:29,140 --> 00:17:29,860
Shaohua,

452
00:17:31,060 --> 00:17:32,500
when I get my paycheck next month,

453
00:17:32,700 --> 00:17:33,540
- I'll pay you back.
- Don't.

454
00:17:34,260 --> 00:17:35,340
You don't earn much.

455
00:17:35,500 --> 00:17:36,460
Better save it for socializing.

456
00:17:37,220 --> 00:17:37,860
Also,

457
00:17:38,180 --> 00:17:40,380
let's not be so formal between us.

458
00:17:41,740 --> 00:17:42,380
Dig in.

459
00:17:52,100 --> 00:17:52,860
Shaohua.

460
00:17:54,740 --> 00:17:55,940
I heard something

461
00:17:56,300 --> 00:17:57,460
at the Tian family's place today.

462
00:18:00,380 --> 00:18:02,020
[Rongshun Restaurant]

463
00:18:03,140 --> 00:18:04,820
Mr. Yang, please.

464
00:18:04,820 --> 00:18:05,420
Okay.

465
00:18:08,700 --> 00:18:09,460
Mr. Yang.

466
00:18:09,700 --> 00:18:10,700
Xia Yuan.

467
00:18:11,660 --> 00:18:13,020
I didn't expect you to arrive so soon.

468
00:18:13,740 --> 00:18:15,660
The second I got your telegram,

469
00:18:15,700 --> 00:18:18,140
I rushed right over.

470
00:18:18,700 --> 00:18:19,780
You must be tired from the journey.

471
00:18:20,340 --> 00:18:21,500
Not at all.

472
00:18:22,060 --> 00:18:25,340
Thanks to your careful planning,

473
00:18:25,620 --> 00:18:27,580
it was a smooth ride.

474
00:18:28,300 --> 00:18:29,060
That's good.

475
00:18:29,420 --> 00:18:30,300
Come, please come inside.

476
00:18:30,300 --> 00:18:31,220
Okay, please.

477
00:18:33,660 --> 00:18:34,340
Please take the head seat.

478
00:18:34,340 --> 00:18:34,940
Okay.

479
00:18:39,420 --> 00:18:40,020
Mr. Yang.

480
00:18:40,500 --> 00:18:41,340
I'd like to propose a toast to you.

481
00:18:48,820 --> 00:18:50,300
If I'm not mistaken,

482
00:18:51,660 --> 00:18:54,140
Mr. Yang, the last time we met

483
00:18:54,460 --> 00:18:56,340
was three years ago in Qizhou.

484
00:18:59,180 --> 00:19:00,260
Xia Yuan.

485
00:19:00,860 --> 00:19:02,180
You're a good friend.

486
00:19:02,180 --> 00:19:03,860
No need to be so formal.

487
00:19:04,260 --> 00:19:05,420
Let's handle the business first.

488
00:19:05,820 --> 00:19:07,340
Once that's done,

489
00:19:07,700 --> 00:19:10,980
we'll catch up.

490
00:19:12,900 --> 00:19:14,500
You haven't changed a bit,

491
00:19:14,580 --> 00:19:16,060
just as honest and generous as ever.

492
00:19:18,900 --> 00:19:20,700
You were so eager to have me come here.

493
00:19:21,180 --> 00:19:23,340
Something big must have happened.

494
00:19:24,900 --> 00:19:26,060
To be honest, Mr. Yang,

495
00:19:26,780 --> 00:19:28,980
I asked you
to come all the way to Shanghai

496
00:19:29,740 --> 00:19:31,700
because I need you
to help me identify someone.

497
00:19:32,140 --> 00:19:32,780
Who?

498
00:19:39,860 --> 00:19:41,780
I hear he used to be in Northeast China

499
00:19:42,140 --> 00:19:44,060
and that he loves to drink baijiu.

500
00:19:47,700 --> 00:19:48,460
Take a look.

501
00:19:49,780 --> 00:19:52,500
Does he look like Glebov?

502
00:19:54,780 --> 00:19:56,460
Yeah, that's Glebov.

503
00:19:58,180 --> 00:19:59,420
Who is Glebov?

504
00:20:00,060 --> 00:20:02,020
A White Russian
who ran a clinic in Shenyang.

505
00:20:02,020 --> 00:20:04,180
He's Russian

506
00:20:04,540 --> 00:20:05,660
and used to be a military doctor.

507
00:20:06,620 --> 00:20:09,500
Back in 1918,

508
00:20:09,980 --> 00:20:11,020
he arrived in Shenyang

509
00:20:11,180 --> 00:20:13,060
and opened a small clinic.

510
00:20:13,780 --> 00:20:15,660
He was really good with business,

511
00:20:15,940 --> 00:20:18,620
and he attracted
a lot of Chinese customers.

512
00:20:19,180 --> 00:20:21,780
He even sourced medicinal herbs from me.

513
00:20:22,020 --> 00:20:24,140
My subordinates all know him.

514
00:20:26,340 --> 00:20:27,260
And what about him now?

515
00:20:27,460 --> 00:20:28,180
Now?

516
00:20:29,900 --> 00:20:31,740
I don't know.

517
00:20:32,100 --> 00:20:34,660
We haven't been in touch for years.

518
00:20:35,300 --> 00:20:36,580
I heard

519
00:20:36,980 --> 00:20:38,900
that his daughter ran off
with a Chinese man.

520
00:20:39,100 --> 00:20:40,380
To find his daughter,

521
00:20:40,380 --> 00:20:41,700
he closed his clinic,

522
00:20:41,700 --> 00:20:42,740
and then came to Shanghai.

523
00:20:47,100 --> 00:20:48,740
[Jujing Apothecary]

524
00:20:48,780 --> 00:20:51,180
Let's ask Mr. Yang to testify in court

525
00:20:51,900 --> 00:20:54,020
to prove that Professor Claudy

526
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:55,540
is a fake.

527
00:20:56,220 --> 00:20:57,100
If that happens,

528
00:20:57,180 --> 00:20:59,740
not only will they lose the lawsuit,

529
00:20:59,740 --> 00:21:01,700
but even Mr. Tian's Western Bunao Pill

530
00:21:01,700 --> 00:21:02,900
will be pulled from the market.

531
00:21:04,380 --> 00:21:07,980
But Mr. Yang
is a business partner of Mr. Xia,

532
00:21:08,020 --> 00:21:10,620
who is a shareholder of Wen's Pharmacy.

533
00:21:10,980 --> 00:21:12,500
Therefore, his testimony

534
00:21:12,860 --> 00:21:14,340
won't be accepted
by the presiding judge.

535
00:21:14,540 --> 00:21:16,380
What if we send someone
to America for evidence?

536
00:21:16,940 --> 00:21:17,660
It would be too late.

537
00:21:17,780 --> 00:21:19,020
The trial starts next week.

538
00:21:19,420 --> 00:21:21,380
What if we get someone
from Tian's Apothecary to testify?

539
00:21:21,460 --> 00:21:22,980
The presiding judge
would surely believe them, right?

540
00:21:23,140 --> 00:21:24,460
Why would

541
00:21:24,460 --> 00:21:26,300
they testify for us?

542
00:21:27,060 --> 00:21:28,180
Didn't you just say

543
00:21:28,780 --> 00:21:31,380
Mr. Tian fired Claudy's assistant?

544
00:21:31,380 --> 00:21:33,100
Maybe we can get him on our side.

545
00:21:34,460 --> 00:21:35,540
That could work.

546
00:22:02,220 --> 00:22:03,020
I know you.

547
00:22:04,140 --> 00:22:04,980
I lost my job

548
00:22:04,980 --> 00:22:06,180
because of you.

549
00:22:08,460 --> 00:22:09,220
I'm sorry.

550
00:22:12,260 --> 00:22:14,300
I have elderly parents to care for,
and young children to raise.

551
00:22:14,300 --> 00:22:15,180
There are six mouths
to feed in my family.

552
00:22:15,180 --> 00:22:16,780
This paycheck is all I have.

553
00:22:17,900 --> 00:22:18,660
And now, just like that,

554
00:22:19,180 --> 00:22:20,340
Mr. Tian fired me.

555
00:22:20,340 --> 00:22:21,780
So what now?
How are we supposed to get by?

556
00:22:24,460 --> 00:22:25,380
I can help you.

557
00:22:28,980 --> 00:22:29,780
How?

558
00:22:30,460 --> 00:22:31,140
Money?

559
00:22:31,260 --> 00:22:33,140
Or do you want a job

560
00:22:33,140 --> 00:22:34,460
better than your previous one?

561
00:22:36,460 --> 00:22:37,860
What do you mean?

562
00:22:39,060 --> 00:22:40,860
As long as you're willing
to testify in court...

563
00:22:41,940 --> 00:22:42,860
I don't know what you're talking about.

564
00:22:43,620 --> 00:22:45,140
This is no longer a secret.

565
00:22:45,700 --> 00:22:47,860
I know he is Glebov,

566
00:22:47,940 --> 00:22:49,060
a White Russian military doctor.

567
00:22:52,780 --> 00:22:53,660
How did you find out?

568
00:22:55,180 --> 00:22:56,380
Take a seat, please.

569
00:22:59,860 --> 00:23:02,300
As long as you're willing to testify,

570
00:23:02,900 --> 00:23:05,340
you and your family
will be well taken care of.

571
00:23:39,780 --> 00:23:40,380
Mr. Tian.

572
00:23:48,460 --> 00:23:49,540
They fell for it.

